All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractHealthCentre
Abstract class representing the core logic of a healthcare simulation.
ArrivalProcess
The ArrivalProcess class models the process of generating arrival events in the simulation.
Bernoulli
A random number generator based on the Bernoulli distribution.
Beta
A random number generator based on the beta distribution.
BetaPrime
A random number generator based on the beta prime distribution.
Binomial
A random number generator based on the Binomial distribution.
Cauchy
A random number generator based on the Cauchy distribution.
ChiSquare
A random number generator based on the Chi-Square distribution.
Clock
The Clock class represents a simulation clock that keeps track of the current simulation time.
ContinuousGenerator
A continuous generator provides a double value according to the distribution it relies on.
DataController
The DataController class is for managing data operations related to probabilities, distributions, and simulation results.
DiscreteGenerator
A continuous generator provides a long value according to the distribution it relies on.
Distribution
Represents a distribution entity for an event in the simulation.
DistributionDao
Provides methods to persist, find, update and delete Distribution records in the database.
Distributions
offers several discrete and continuous distributions all seeded by a common well-spaced pseudo random number generator (PRNG).
Erlang
A random number generator based on the Erlang distribution.
Event
The Event class represents an event in the simulation, characterized by its type and the time it occurs.
EventList
The EventList class manages a list of simulation events using a priority queue.
EventType
Enumeration representing the various event types in the simulation.
FDistribution
A random number generator based on the F-distribution.
Gamma
A random number generator based on the normal distribution.
Generator
A generic Generator class which delegates its Seedable ability to a Distributions object.
Geometric
A random number generator based on the geometric distribution.
HealthcenterController
The HealthcenterController class is for managing the health center simulation.
HealthcenterGUI
The main graphical user interface (GUI) class for the Health Center simulation application.
HealthCentre
The HealthCentre class models a healthcare center simulation, handling patient flow between various service points, such as check-in, doctor consultation, lab, x-ray, and treatment.
IControllerForP
Interface for controlling actions related to the patient in the health center simulation.
IControllerForV
Interface for controlling the health center simulation from the user interface.
IDataControlller
Interface for controlling data operations related to probabilities, distributions and simulation results.
IEventType
The IEventType interface is a marker interface used to define event types in the simulation.
IHealthcenterGUI
The IHealthcenterGUI interface defines the methods required for the graphical user interface of the health center simulation.
IHealthCentre
The IHealthCentre interface defines the methods that must be implemented by any class representing a health center in the simulation.
Invgamma
A random number generator based on the invgamma distribution.
IVisualization
The IVisualization interface defines methods for visualizing patient flow in the simulation.
Logistic
A random number generator based on the logistic distribution.
LogNormal
A random number generator based on the lognormal distribution.
Main
The main class for starting the Healthcenter simulation application
MariaDbJpaConnection
Singleton class for managing the EntityManager instance for MariaDB.
MetaGenerator
A class which allows for automatically parsing a distribution implementation and generate a class inheriting from Generator accordingly.
Negexp
A random number generator based on the negexp distribution.
Normal
A random number generator based on the normal distribution.
ParameterException
Error thrown when a distribution is passed incorrect parameters.
Pareto
A random number generator based on the pareto distribution.
Pascal
A random number generator based on the pascal distribution.
Patient
The Patient class represents a patient in the healthcare simulation.
Poisson
A random number generator based on the poisson distribution.
Probability
The Probability class represents a decision probability in the simulation.
ProbabilityDao
Provides methods to persist, find, update and delete probability records in the database.
RandomGenerator
A random number generator producing pseudorandom numbers based on the value of a specific seed.
SampleGenerator
 
Seedable
represents classes which has a seed
SeedGenerator
A SeedGenerator is a DiscreteGenerator which produces well-spaced seeds according to its spacing attribute.
ServicePoint
The ServicePoint class represents a point in the healthcare simulation where patients receive services.
SimulationResults
The SimulationResults class represents the results of a simulation run.
SimulationResultsDao
Provides methods to persist, find, update and delete records of Simulation Results in the database.
Trace
The Trace class is used to log and output messages in the simulation at different levels.
Trace.Level
Enum representing the different trace levels: INFO, WAR (Warning), and ERR (Error).
Tstudent
A random number generator based on the tstudent distribution.
Uniform
A random number generator based on the uniform distribution.
Visualization
The Visualization class provides the graphical representation of patients in the simulation using a canvas.
Weibull
A random number generator based on the weibull distribution.
